HEADWORD: Plasson
<hw>Plas"son</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/
to form.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The albuminous material
composing the body of a cytode.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It is considered simpler than protoplasm of an ordinary
cell in that it has not undergone differentiation into the inner cell
nucleus and the outer cell substance.</note>
<rj><au>Haeckel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plaster</ent>⟦br⟧
